HEADWORD: Polytomous
<hw>Po*lyt"o*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a cutting, fr. <?/ to cut.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Subdivided into many distinct subordinate parts,
which, however, not being jointed to the petiole, are not true leaflets;
-- said of leaves.</def> <rj><au>Henslow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

